{
  "stem": "2004.2",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But by and large, we lived within that designated area, and we had a what we call a Jewish community.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Now, that Jewish community was in charge for work details.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "The Germans needed a certain group of people to do work outside the ghetto, wherever they needed us.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "So it was the responsibility of the Jewish committee to supply these workers.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I was assigned-- I was at the time already 15 years old.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Now, we are now coming into 1942.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "We are now somewhere in the late spring, early summer of 1942.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "I was assigned to work in a German lumber yard.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "I do remember the name.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "The name of the lumber yard was Hobach Holzbau, which means it's a lumber yard that was not actually-- this was a lumber yard which was owned by a German company.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "The name of the company was Hobach which is really an abbreviation of Holzbau, Ho-bach, first two letters.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Holz meaning wood, bau means building, so sort of a building.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "Now, their primary function was to build barracks for the German army.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "They were building parts of barracks, which were then shipped to wherever the soldiers needed them, and they were assembled on site.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "Preassembled barracks.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And I worked in that part together with a group of other people.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "I believe we were at that time possibly 50 or 60 young men that were working in that Hobach Holzbau, which was managed by a German with a big dog, a big shepherd, German Shepherd.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] And he kept law and order with that dog.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "If somebody was out of line, went out of line, that dog took care of you.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
